<article>
    <h1>See the lights in Lit&#xAD;tle In&#xAD;dia on a tr&#xAD;ishaw</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201110/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-10"><time>2020-11-10</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE TRAVEL</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Lit­tle In­dia has, ar­guably, the best lights display out of all the fes­tive decor that goes up in the var­i­ous neigh­bour­hoods over the year.</p>
    <p>The In­dian Her­itage Cen­tre has or­gan­ised the best way to see the lights as part of its Deep­avali cel­e­bra­tions: in a zippy 15-minute ride in a tr­ishaw.</p>
    <p>The tour starts in front of the cen­tre in Camp­bell Lane, goes through Up­per Dick­son, then hits the stretch of Seran­goon Road un­til Row­ell Road be­fore cir­cling over to Jalan Be­sar and back to the cen­tre via Dun­lop Street.</p>
    <p>Be­sides the lights, you also get to see all the lit­tle al­leys full of eater­ies be­tween Seran­goon and Jalan Be­sar – great way to note down new food places to check out.</p>
    <p>Un­for­tu­nately, the ride is avail­able only on Fri­days and this Fri­day is the last chance to catch a ride with Tr­ishaw Un­cle.</p>
    <p>The ride is free but a re­fund­able de­posit of $10 and reg­is­tra­tion is re­quired. Sign up at str.sg/Ju7T</p>

